## /auth/me/kyc

This endpoint is used to submit KYC (Know Your Customer) information.

### Request

- Method: POST

- Body (form-data):

    - No parameters provided in the request body


### Response

- Status: 200

- Content-Type: application/json

- { "success": true}


### JSON Schema for Response

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Auth Check Email

This endpoint is used to check the availability of an email for authentication.

#### Request

- Method: POST

- URL: {{Url}}/auth/check-email

- Body:

    - email (text, required): The email to be checked for availability.


#### Response

The response for this request is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "errors": {
      "type": "array"
    },
    "full_messages": {
      "type": "array"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains the following fields:

- success (boolean): Indicates whether the email is available.

- errors (array): An array of error messages, if any.

- full_messages (array): An array of full messages, if any.

- Status: 404

- Content-Type: application/json

### Verify Reset Password OTP

The `POST` request is used to verify the OTP (One Time Password) for resetting the password associated with a specific email.

#### Request Body

- `email` (string, required): The email address for which the OTP is being verified.

- `otp` (string, required): The One Time Password to be verified.


#### Response

The response will be in JSON format and will conform to the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "status": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

- `status` (string): Indicates the status of the OTP verification process.

- `message` (string): Provides additional information about the verification status.

